1. Open Terminal and go to your folder
bashcd ~/Downloads
2. Activate the virtual environment
bashsource venv/bin/activate
Your prompt will change to show (venv) — that means it's active.
3. Edit your hostnames file
bashnano hostnames.txt
One hostname per line, # to comment out a line. Ctrl+O → Enter to save, Ctrl+X to exit.
4. Dry run first — see what would be deleted without touching anything
bashpython delete_zabbix_hosts.py -f hostnames.txt -n firstname.lastname --dry-run
5. Run the actual delete
bashpython delete_zabbix_hosts.py -f hostnames.txt -n firstname.lastname --workers 3
6. When done, deactivate the environment
bashdeactivate

Optional flags to remember:
FlagWhat it does
--workers 33 parallel deletes at a time (safe for slow servers)
--timeout 300 Wait up to 300s per delete before giving up--dry-runPreview only, no deletes-n firstname.lastnameYour Zabbix username

If you get a password prompt every time and want to avoid it, run this once:
bashpython -c "import keyring; keyring.set_password('zabbix', 'firstname.lastname', 'yourpassword')"
After that, the script pulls your password from the macOS keychain automatically
